        "subject": "LU-11836 ldlm: fix enqueue reply vs bl_ast race",
        "message": "LU-11836 ldlm: fix enqueue reply vs bl_ast race\n\nIn general this race may occur when enqueue replies with\nreplaced lock resource and BL AST happens at the same time\non that lock. If BL AST arrives on client earlier than\nenqueue reply then callback will be called on parent lock\nwith no cancel returned to the server causing lock timeout.\nMoreover, if lost enqueue reply will be resend that may\ncause deadlock:\n- enqueue #1 issues lock on server but with resend\n- process #2 cause BL AST to it before resend\n- enqueue #1 resend will wait for parent lock on server\n- process #2 holds parent lock busy waiting for cancel\n  which will never come. Deadlock\n\nThis situations are very rare but become visible with DOM\nbecause it uses more conflicting lock modes and read-on-open\nmay cause resends due to buffer grow on server.\n\nSigned-off-by: Mikhail Pershin <mpershin@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Id11a5e1bb6266ae3c6d35b0157774281c1e49d5a\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
